The drain path itself is straightforward and doesn’t need external swap routes: by setting `targetToken` to one of the position’s own pool tokens, the callback will forward both withdrawn assets directly to `instructions.recipient`. The hard part is narrower: finding a real mainnet position where the approved operator at block `16653389` is either our contract or a permissionless/public operator we can drive from our PoC.
